        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\mathsf {NatInd}}\ P\ mz\ ms\ ({\mathsf {suc}}\ n)\equiv ms\ n\ (NatInd\ P\ mz\ ms\ n)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b91f59f375d2ad9512dd69fe8a7ebdb09406e5e9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:54.489ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\mathsf {NatInd}}\ P\ mz\ ms\ ({\mathsf {suc}}\ n)\equiv ms\ n\ (NatInd\ P\ mz\ ms\ n)" /></span></p>
<p>...And in ASCII:</p>
<pre>
NatInd : all P : Nat -&gt; * =&gt; P zero -&gt;
         (all n : Nat =&gt; P n -&gt; P (suc n)) -&gt;
         all n : Nat =&gt; P n
NatInd P mz ms zero =&gt; mz
NatInd P mz ms (suc n) =&gt; ms n (NatInd P mz ms n)
</pre>
